Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveVice President Yemi Osinbajo has shared photos from the moment, he paid his respect at the tomb of Nigeria’s sole Prime Minister, Sir Abubakar Tafawa Balewa.
Osinbajo shared photos on his Facebook page on Wednesday, saying, “At the tomb of Alhaji Sir Abubakar Tafawa Balewa, the first and only Prime Minister of Nigeria to pay respect as we visited Bauchi.”
The VP has been touring Nigeria to visit delegates of the ruling All Progressives Congress, whose presidential ticket he is seeking.
